Long-lost childhood friends Josh Smith (vocals, guitar, production) and Josh Freed (beats, electronics, production) reconnected in 2014 and began writing their debut album Window on borrowed equipment, recording in vacant spaces and mixing in friends’ cars. With a keen ability to mesh together seemingly random sounds, GOSH PITH earned early critical attention from The Guardian, Stereogum, Noisey, Pigeons and Planes, and the like, and racked up millions of plays across the internet.
